{{Infobox figure skater |name= Grace Madden |image= |caption= |fullname= Grace E. Madden |altname= |country= [[United States]] |formercountry= |birth_date= {{birth date|1911|7|30}} |birth_place= [[Marblehead, Massachusetts]] |hometown= |residence= |death_date= {{death date and age|1987|6|14|1911|7|30}} |death_place= [[Darien, Connecticut]] |height= |partner= |formerpartner= [[J. Lester Madden]] |coach= |formercoach= |choreographer= |formerchoreographer= |skating club= [[SC of Boston]] |retired= |medaltemplates= <!-- see [[Template:MedalRelatedTemplates]] --> {{MedalCountry| [[United States]]}} {{MedalSport | Pairs [[Figure skating]]}} {{MedalCompetition|[[North American Figure Skating Championships|North American Championships]]}} {{MedalBronze|[[1937 North American Figure Skating Championships|1937 Boston]]|[[1937 North American Figure Skating Championships|Pairs]]}} }} '''Grace E. Madden''' ([[married name]]: Ward; born July 30, 1911 in [[Marblehead, Massachusetts]], died June 14, 1987 in [[Darien, Connecticut]]) was an [[United States|American]] [[pair skater]]. With brother [[J. Lester Madden]], she was the 1934 [[U.S. Figure Skating Championships|U.S. national champion]]. They competed at the [[1936 Winter Olympics]] and placed 11th.
